post_text: It’s official!! Alma will be hosting its' first ever Alma Band Day Parade on Saturday, October 17, at 1 PM. The parade will be a bands only parade, no floats or other entries, and invitations have been sent to schools all over the south central Nebraska area. We don’t yet know how many schools are willing/able to come for sure, but do have about 10 bands already showing interest or who have said they are coming for sure. The parade will be a competition and will be judged by three outstanding judges, two former UNK band directors, Dr. Gary Davis and Dr. Ron Crocker, and retired Kearney music teacher Dave Klein. The parade will run from the Johnson Center on Main Street all the way to the end of the park. An award ceremony will be held in the park at the conclusion of the parade. Both the Alma Jr and Sr high band will be marching in the parade. More details will follow but we we wanted to make sure everyone gets this on their calendar as it should be a fun day of music!

post_text: Just a reminder that Two Rivers Public Health Department will be administering flu shots to students at Alma Public Schools on Friday, September 11. Please complete one entire packet for EACH student you want to get their flu shot. The completed packet must be returned by August 28. On another note, we will not restrain students in order to administer the shot. If your child comes to get their shot and refuses they will be sent back to class unless you, as the parent, want to come to school to restrain your child. We are excited to provide this opportunity for our students!! Share to be aware! #ProudToBeACardinal

Congratulations to Madison Schuller on being named as a recipient of the Western Nebraska Administrators Scholarship for use in the upcoming 2020-2021 school year.

The WNA is a group of school administrators from across the Panhandle, West Central and Southwest Nebraska who advocate for public education in Nebraska. Each year they offer scholarships for the second semester to qualifying students who are pursuing a career in the field of education. Way to go Madi!! #ProudToBeACardinal

post_text:
Happy summer students and parents!! We have officially made it! Congrats to you and your kiddos for pulling through and finishing the school year strong. We are all experiencing a different start to summer but don’t forget that our brains still need to be exercised along with our bodies. K-3 teachers are sending home summer packets to encourage students to keep learning.
Parents of any age student, let your children read, read read! Be fascinated with them as they want to learn about new things. Show an interest yourself in wanting to learn. We are never to old to learn!
K-6 parents, if you are wanting ideas or more paper copies of things for your children to do, please contact Mrs. Lukas at sally.lukas@almacardinals.org. Have a wonderful summer!!

post_text:
Tonight would have been the 6th annual Cardinal Youth Choir banquet. This fundraiser is usually the highlight of the year for the elementary choir kids and it has been disappointing to have to close the year without their normal celebration! Mrs. Fritz and this year’s choir kids wanted to share a little something of what they were preparing. The choir kids sent Mrs. Fritz an audio recording of one of the songs they had been working on and Mrs. Fritz put them together. Even though their time working together got cut short, and they didn’t have a director to watch or fancy recording equipment, they still wanted to celebrate all they had done this year. Mrs. Fritz also was able to deliver this year’s choir awards and the winners are featured in the video. A special thank you to this year’s 6th grade choir members. You will be missed!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yJMWuLclEMg #ProudToBeACardinal

post_text:
Alma Public School is pleased to announce that we have had three students awarded Susan Thompson Buffett Foundation scholarships. Each of these students has worked hard throughout high school and we are excited to see them receive such a generous award!

The scholarship recipients from Alma are:
Bonnie Nelson, daughter of Angel and the late Scott Nelson, granddaughter of Sharon Nelson
William Anderson, son of Edward Anderson and Tina Gdowski
Michael Edgar whose guardians are Justin and Jaclyn Daake

The Susan T. Buffett Foundation has offered scholarships to college students in Nebraska for over 50 years. Scholarships are awarded on a competitive basis to first-time freshmen entering college who are residents of Nebraska, graduates of a Nebraska high school (or GED) with plans to attend a Nebraska public college.

Congratulations!! #ProudToBeACardinal
